Description: NextPVR media player client (Wayland, system libmpv)
 yauiclient is a 10-foot-UI media player client for NextPVR. This flavour
 targets Wayland sessions and uses the system-installed libmpv2 instead
 of bundling its own. Recommended for users who already have a working
 mpv install and prefer to keep one libmpv on their system.
 .
 NOTE: this flavour declares only 'Depends: libmpv2' with no version
 constraint. The yauiclient Wayland integration relies on GLFW 3.4 plus
 a libmpv ABI close to 0.36+; older mpv versions (Ubuntu 24.04 ships
 mpv 0.35, Debian 12 ships mpv 0.35) may exhibit playback issues. If you
 hit problems, switch to yauiclient-wayland which bundles libmpv 0.41.
 .
 This package installs to /usr/bin/yauiclient and conflicts with the other
 yauiclient flavours; only one can be installed at a time.
